.TH "nfs_set_verifier" 9 "nfs_set_verifier" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
nfs_set_verifier \- save a parent directory verifier in the dentry
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" nfs_set_verifier
.BI "(struct dentry *dentry "  ","
.BI "unsigned long verf "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dentry" 12
pointer to dentry
.IP "verf" 12
verifier to save
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Saves the parent directory verifier in \fIdentry\fP. If the inode has
a delegation, we also tag the dentry as having been revalidated
while holding a delegation so that we know we don't have to
look it up again after a directory change.
